<paragraph id="776B36D0FFBBD33CFF66FAE03F19FC2B" blockId="2.[187,1398,926,987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">
Characterized by the 
<taxonomicName id="B0D44D53FFBBD33CFE75FAE03865FC48" box="[430,521,926,952]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="45A0EAC2FFBBD33CFE75FAE03865FC48" box="[430,521,926,952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Trechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like body shape, but without elongate frontal furrows, by elongate and acute terminal palpomeres, and by the wide, depressed, usually pilose subapical marginal channel of the elytra.
</paragraph>
